.TH "BSON_VALIDATE" "3" "Aug 31, 2022" "1.23.0" "libbson"
.SH NAME
bson_validate \- bson_validate()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
bool
bson_validate (const bson_t *bson, bson_validate_flags_t flags, size_t *offset);
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH PARAMETERS
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBbson\fP: A \fI\%bson_t\fP\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBflags\fP: A bitwise\-or of all desired \fI\%bson_validate_flags_t\fP\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBoffset\fP: A location for the offset within \fBbson\fP where the error occurred.
.UNINDENT
.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
Validates a BSON document by walking through the document and inspecting the keys and values for valid content.
.sp
You can modify how the validation occurs through the use of the \fBflags\fP parameter, see \fI\%bson_validate_with_error()\fP for details.
.SH RETURNS
.sp
Returns true if \fBbson\fP is valid; otherwise false and \fBoffset\fP is set to the byte offset where the error was detected.
.sp
\fBSEE ALSO:\fP
